---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Uses | Joe Karlsson" description="Hardware, software, and gear I use daily for development, content creation, and my homelab.">
	<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-8">
		<h1 class="mb-2 text-4xl font-bold md:text-5xl">
			<span class="text-coral">Uses</span>
		</h1>
		<p class="mb-2 text-lg text-gray-400">
			Hardware, software, and gear I use daily for development, content creation, and running my homelab.
		</p>
		<p class="mb-8 text-sm text-gray-500">Last updated: March 2026</p>

		<img
			src="/images/blog/how-i-work/IMG_2685.jpg"
			alt="Joe Karlsson's desk setup"
			class="mb-10 w-full rounded-lg border border-surface-3"
			loading="eager"
		/>

		<!-- Desk Setup -->
		<section class="mb-10">
			<h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-teal">Desk Setup</h2>
			<div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300">
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Computer</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">MacBook Pro with Apple M3 Pro chip and 36 GB of RAM. A massive upgrade from the M1 Air &mdash; the extra cores and memory make a real difference for Docker, multiple IDEs, and running local AI models.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Monitors</h3>
					<ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-gray-400">
						<li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Lenovo-ThinkVision-P27h-10-LED-Monitor/dp/B071DK1TW8" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">ThinkVision P27h-10</a> 27-inch Wide QHD IPS Type-C Monitor (right side)</li>
						<li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Dell-U2723QE-UltraSharp-USB-C-Monitor/dp/B09TQZP9CL" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Dell U3417W</a> 34-inch 4K Monitor (left side)</li>
						<li>If I were picking up a monitor today, I'd probably go ultrawide.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Monitor Arm</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Ergotron LX Dual Monitor Arm. I like being able to move my monitors around based on what I'm working on and to free up space for hardware projects.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Dock</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Dell-452-BCYT-D6000-Universal-Black/dp/B071YTQBXM" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Dell Universal Dock D6000</a> &mdash; bought used on eBay for under $100. Single USB-C cable for power, monitors, and all USB accessories.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Input Devices</h3>
					<ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-gray-400">
						<li>Razer DeathAdder Chroma gaming mouse</li>
						<li>Apple Magic Trackpad 2 for swipe and pinch controls</li>
						<li>Razer Goliathus Extended Chroma mousepad</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Desk & Seating</h3>
					<ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-gray-400">
						<li>Custom-built standing desktop: IKEA desktop on industrial black steel legs</li>
						<li>Luna Standing Desk Stool for staying active while working</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Audio</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Sony-MDR7506-Professional-Diaphragm-Headphone/dp/B000AJIF4E" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Sony MDR7506</a> Professional Large Diaphragm Headphones with upgraded velvet pads. Affordable, comfortable, and sound great.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Lighting</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400"><a href="https://www.bestbuy.com/site/philips-hue-play-white-color-ambiance-smart-led-bar-light-2-pack-multicolor/6298635.p" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Philips Hue Play</a> White & Color Ambiance LED Bar Lights (2-Pack) for desk backlighting.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="mt-4 grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
				<img src="/images/blog/how-i-work/IMG_2687-1024x576.jpg" alt="Desk setup angle 1" class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3" loading="lazy" />
				<img src="/images/blog/how-i-work/IMG_2688-1024x576.jpg" alt="Desk setup angle 2" class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3" loading="lazy" />
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Recording -->
		<section class="mb-10">
			<h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-teal">Recording & Streaming</h2>
			<div class="space-y-3">
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Webcam</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400"><a href="https://www.obsbot.com/obsbot-tiny-2" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">OBSBOT Tiny 2</a> &mdash; 4K AI-powered webcam with gesture control and auto-tracking. Replaced my Sony A6600 &mdash; much simpler setup for Zoom calls and recordings.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Streaming</h3>
					<ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-gray-400">
						<li><a href="https://www.elgato.com/en/gaming/stream-deck" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Elgato Stream Deck</a> for controlling streams and shortcuts</li>
						<li><a href="https://obsproject.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">OBS (Open Broadcaster Software)</a> for streaming</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Microphone</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400"><a href="https://www.elgato.com/us/en/p/wave-3-black" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Elgato Wave:3</a> USB condenser microphone, managed through <a href="https://www.elgato.com/us/en/s/wave-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Wave Link</a> for mixing. Replaced the Blue Yeti &mdash; much better sound quality and integrates with the rest of the Elgato ecosystem.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Lighting & Green Screen</h3>
					<ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-gray-400">
						<li>Two <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B07L755X9G" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Elgato Key Lights</a> plus professional studio LED panels</li>
						<li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00JSAOGWG" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Fancierstudio Collapsible Green/Blue Screen</a> on a <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00PLEX7Q4" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Fovitec 7'6" Clip Stand</a></li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Keyboard -->
		<section class="mb-10">
			<h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-teal">Keyboards</h2>
			<img
				src="/images/blog/how-i-work/5422ABA8-496F-41FD-83A0-E04FD7807046-1024x823.jpg"
				alt="Joe's mechanical keyboards"
				class="mb-4 w-full rounded-lg border border-surface-3"
				loading="lazy"
			/>
			<div class="space-y-3">
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Vortexgear Race 3</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B072LZ2YRM" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Vortexgear Race 3</a> with Cherry MX Clear switches.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Custom Vortex POK3R</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Custom-built with a wood case, Cherry MX Blue switches, and a custom keycap set from WASD Keyboards. I like clicky switches &mdash; Blues are the loudest and clickiest. I'd recommend Clears as a good starter switch.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Editor & Terminal -->
		<section class="mb-10">
			<h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-teal">Editor & Terminal</h2>
			<div class="space-y-3">
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Code Editors</h3>
					<ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-gray-400">
						<li><a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Visual Studio Code</a> &mdash; still my primary editor</li>
						<li><a href="https://www.cursor.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Cursor</a> &mdash; AI-powered fork of VS Code, increasingly my go-to for new projects</li>
						<li>Monokai color theme + <a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=vscode-icons-team.vscode-icons" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">vscode-icons</a> icon theme</li>
						<li><a href="https://wakatime.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">WakaTime</a> &mdash; like a Fitbit for programmers, automated time tracking and metrics</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Key VS Code Extensions</h3>
					<ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-gray-400">
						<li><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=eamodio.gitlens" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">GitLens</a> &mdash; supercharged git blame and history</li>
						<li><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=esbenp.prettier-vscode" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Prettier</a> + <a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=dbaeumer.vscode-eslint" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">ESLint</a> &mdash; formatting and linting</li>
						<li><a href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=github.copilot-chat" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">GitHub Copilot</a> &mdash; AI pair programming</li>
						<li>Docker, Remote SSH, Remote Containers &mdash; for working inside LXC containers</li>
						<li>Go, Python, Svelte language support</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">AI Tools</h3>
					<ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-gray-400">
						<li><a href="https://claude.ai/download" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Claude</a> desktop app &mdash; writing, research, and brainstorming</li>
						<li><a href="https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Claude Code</a> (CLI) &mdash; my primary coding companion. I use it in the terminal for everything from infrastructure automation to building this website. It manages my homelab, writes deployment scripts, and helps debug across 40+ containers.</li>
						<li><a href="https://github.com/features/copilot" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">GitHub Copilot</a> &mdash; inline code completion in VS Code and Cursor</li>
						<li><a href="https://superwhisper.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">superwhisper</a> &mdash; local speech-to-text, great for dictating docs and messages</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Terminal</h3>
					<ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-gray-400">
						<li><a href="https://iterm2.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">iTerm2</a></li>
						<li><a href="https://ohmyz.sh/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Oh My Zsh</a> with <a href="https://github.com/romkatv/powerlevel10k" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Powerlevel10k</a> theme</li>
						<li>Plugins: git, z (directory jumping), zsh-autosuggestions, zsh-syntax-highlighting</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Dotfiles</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">You can find most of my config files over at my <a href="https://github.com/JoeKarlsson/dotfiles" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">dotfiles repo</a> on GitHub.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Apps -->
		<section class="mb-10">
			<h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-teal">Apps</h2>
			<div class="grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2">
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Productivity</h3>
					<ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-gray-400">
						<li><a href="https://www.raycast.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Raycast</a> &mdash; launcher, snippets, clipboard history</li>
						<li><a href="https://apps.apple.com/us/app/magnet/id441258766?mt=12" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Magnet</a> &mdash; window management</li>
						<li>Apple Reminders + self-hosted CalDAV via <a href="https://nextcloud.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Nextcloud</a> &mdash; tasks and calendar sync without iCloud</li>
						<li><a href="https://www.notion.so/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Notion</a> &mdash; notes and docs</li>
						<li><a href="https://linear.app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Linear</a> &mdash; issue tracking</li>
						<li><a href="https://grammarly.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Grammarly</a> &mdash; writing assistant</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Communication & Social</h3>
					<ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-gray-400">
						<li><a href="https://rambox.pro/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Rambox</a> &mdash; all messaging clients in one app</li>
						<li><a href="https://discord.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Discord</a></li>
						<li><a href="https://zoom.us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Zoom</a></li>
						<li><a href="https://github.com/gitroomhq/postiz-app" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Postiz</a> &mdash; self-hosted social media scheduling (replaced Buffer)</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Media & Content</h3>
					<ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-gray-400">
						<li><a href="https://www.plex.tv/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Plex</a> &mdash; media streaming (self-hosted)</li>
						<li>Apple Music</li>
						<li><a href="https://www.videolan.org/vlc/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">VLC</a> &mdash; plays anything</li>
						<li><a href="https://www.techsmith.com/camtasia.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Camtasia</a> &mdash; screen recording and video editing</li>
						<li><a href="https://www.screen.studio/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Screen Studio</a> &mdash; beautiful screen recordings</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Security & Privacy</h3>
					<ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-gray-400">
						<li><a href="https://1password.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">1Password</a> &mdash; password manager (+ self-hosted <a href="https://github.com/dani-garcia/vaultwarden" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Vaultwarden</a> as backup)</li>
						<li><a href="https://tailscale.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Tailscale</a> &mdash; mesh VPN for accessing homelab remotely from anywhere</li>
						<li><a href="https://www.privateinternetaccess.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Private Internet Access</a> &mdash; commercial VPN for privacy on public networks</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Utilities</h3>
					<ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-gray-400">
						<li><a href="https://github.com/dwarvesf/hidden" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Hidden Bar</a> &mdash; hide menu bar icons</li>
						<li><a href="https://rogueamoeba.com/soundsource/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">SoundSource</a> &mdash; per-app audio control</li>
						<li><a href="https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Docker Desktop</a></li>
						<li><a href="https://nextcloud.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Nextcloud</a> &mdash; self-hosted file sync</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Self-Hosted Integrations -->
		<section class="mb-10">
			<h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-teal">Self-Hosted Integrations</h2>
			<p class="mb-4 text-sm text-gray-400">
				One of the best parts of running a homelab is replacing SaaS dependencies with self-hosted alternatives that integrate with each other. Here's how my stack connects:
			</p>
			<div class="space-y-3">
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Photos & Backup</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400"><a href="https://github.com/immich-app/immich" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Immich</a> replaces Google Photos &mdash; auto-uploads from my phone, GPU-accelerated face recognition, and all photos stored on the NAS. No cloud subscription, no storage limits.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Documents & AI</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400"><a href="https://github.com/paperless-ngx/paperless-ngx" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Paperless-ngx</a> ingests all scanned documents with OCR, and <a href="https://github.com/clusterzx/paperless-ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Paperless-AI</a> auto-tags and categorizes them. Mail comes in, gets scanned, and is searchable within minutes.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Calendar & Tasks</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Apple Reminders and Calendar sync to a self-hosted <a href="https://nextcloud.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Nextcloud</a> CalDAV server instead of iCloud. Same native Apple apps, but the data lives on my hardware.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Media Pipeline</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">The Arr stack (<a href="https://github.com/Sonarr/Sonarr" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Sonarr</a>, <a href="https://github.com/Radarr/Radarr" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Radarr</a>, <a href="https://github.com/Prowlarr/Prowlarr" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Prowlarr</a>) manages media acquisition. <a href="https://github.com/HaveAGitGat/Tdarr" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Tdarr</a> transcodes everything to H.265 using the GPUs, saving terabytes of storage. <a href="https://www.plex.tv/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Plex</a> serves it all to every screen in the house.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
					<h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold text-white">Home Security</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-400"><a href="https://github.com/blakeblackshear/frigate" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Frigate</a> runs real-time object detection on security camera feeds using the GPU. Detections trigger automations in <a href="https://www.home-assistant.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-coral hover:text-teal">Home Assistant</a> &mdash; lights, notifications, and recording clips. All processed locally, nothing sent to the cloud.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-surface-3 bg-surface-1 p-5">
